# --- Netlify Proxy Rules ---

# 1. API: Forward all /api requests to AWS
/api/* http://theplug-env.eba-m4aukda5.eu-north-1.elasticbeanstalk.com/api/:splat  200!

# 2. SignalR: Forward the Hub connection
/hubs/* http://theplug-env.eba-m4aukda5.eu-north-1.elasticbeanstalk.com/hubs/:splat  200!

# 3. Images: Forward image requests to the 'uploads' folder on AWS
#    This is CRITICAL for your images to load without Mixed Content errors.
/uploads/* http://theplug-env.eba-m4aukda5.eu-north-1.elasticbeanstalk.com/uploads/:splat  200!

# --- React Router Fallback ---
# 4. Catch-all: Send everything else to index.html so React handles the routing
/* /index.html  200